College_Heading: University of Luebeck, Germany Rankings, Campus, Accommodation, Programs, Admissions, Cost of Attendance and Scholarships
College_Summary: University of Luebeck is a public institution offering several degree programs across the fields of medicine, sciences and research. It is among the top 5 universities in Germany in the competition on Exchanges between Universities and Corporations. Moreover, it was ranked #1 in Medicine and #2 in the Informatics and Molecular Life Science section by The Centre for Development of Higher Education (CHE). The University of Luebeck also is ranked as #660 in the list of Best Global Universities, as per the US News Rankings 2023. The language for teaching is German and a few master’s programs are taught in English. A high number of international students take admission to the University of Luebeck every year.

College_Heading: University of Wuppertal: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: University of Wuppertal is a German research college. It was established in the year 1972, situated in the small city of Wuppertal, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. College_Heading: Witten Herdecke University Germany- Rankings, Campus, Accommodation, Programs, Admissions, Cost of Attendance and Scholarships
College_Summary: Witten/Herdecke University (UW/H) is the first German private institute to receive accreditation as a Universitat. UW/H offers limited courses at UG, PG, and doctoral- level in several academic areas like management and economics, psychology, nursing science, medicine and dentistry. The university’s UG and PG degree programs in Health have been awarded the “Seal of Quality” by the German Psychological Society. In addition, UW/H also contributes to research and is a proud member of an international research network spanning all five continents.

College_Heading: Union College - Schenectady NY, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Union College, Schenectady is a prestigious and one of the oldest higher education colleges in the US. ranked #44 in the national liberal arts colleges by US News, the college is famous for its affordable programs that it offers. The admissions at Union College open up thrice a year in the fall, winter, and summer terms, with no application fee required for the international candidates to apply. The early decision deadline for application is November 1. One of the most famous programs offered at Union College, Schenectady is the MBA, for which the required IELTS and GMAT scores are 6.5 and 500 respectively.

College_Heading: University of Minnesota - Morris: Courses, Rankings, Admission Criteria, Fees & Scholarships
College_Summary: The University of Minnesota Morris is a public university in Minneapolis best known for its undergraduate programs based on liberal arts. It has also ranked among the top 150 liberal arts-based colleges in the USA (US News and World Report). Programs offered at the University of Minnesota Morris include 30+ majors and minors and 9 pre-professional programs.For admission, international students are required to submit GPA over 3.00 and a TOEFL score of 79+. Candidates can also submit a statement of purpose, letters of recommendation and written portfolio Admission at the University of Minnesota Morris is slightly competitive, with an acceptance rate of 65%.
